He said he had rebuked her, saying: 'But do you want to leave seven orphans?'

The Pope said: 'That is an irresponsibility. [That woman might say] 'no but I trust in God.' But God gives you methods to be responsible.' 

He added: 'Some think that in order to be good Catholics we have to be like rabbits. No. Responsible parenthood.'

The remarks immediately provoked anger from pro-life groups who said that they were hurtful to Catholic mothers who had sacrificed careers, time and energy to care for their children.

Former US Republican Presidential candidate Rick Santorum, a devout Catholic, said: 'It's sometimes very difficult to listen to the Pope and some of the things he says off the cuff, and this is one of them.'

The following Wednesday, Pope Francis attempted to repair some of the damage, telling his general audience in St Peter's Square: 'It gives me consolation and hope to see so many large families that welcome children as a true gift from God.'

